@NODE "Ins" "Installation"
@TOC "MAIN"

   Please install the included libraries into your directory LIBS:
   and c/flushtrx into C:
   You can install the rest of this package to any location do you want.

   That's all ;-)

   As next @{"configure" link "Con"} the program values via tooltype.

                                       @{" >>> next >>> " link "Con"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Con" "Configuration"
@TOC "MAIN"

   After @{"installation" link "Ins"} you have to configure the program values.
   Click at £LinkChecker GUI¨ icon. 
   Select workbench menu to manipulate the tooltype of this icon:
         * german  - Piktogramm | Informationen ...
         * english - Icons | Information ...

   The main value you have to configure is your favorite text editor:
         * select "EDITOR"
         * you have to give the name (with path) of your editor
           (e.g. MEmacs)

   Next step:
         * select "REXXCOMMAND"
         * give the ARexx command of your editor to jump directly to the
           line where the broken link can be found
         - the variable "%line" is the option of LinkChecker to hand over the
           line that includes the broken link to the editor
           (e.g. goto %line OPT W)

   You don't have to fill out the other values. They will be automatically set
   while using LinkChecker.

                                       @{" >>> next >>> " link "Usa"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "Usa" "Usage"
@TOC "MAIN"

   Double click the £LinkChecker GUI¨ icon.

   The last versions of LinkChecker has produced fatal errors while analyzing
   an empty main directory. Now you have to select a directory where at least 
   one HTML file is located. Otherwise an error message will be appear.

      @{" The Main Window   " link "MWind"}
      @{" The Result Window " link "RWind"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "MWind" "Usage - Main Window"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{fg shine}The Main Window@{fg text}
   First you can select either to check a complete directory with all
   subdirectories or only one file.
   Below you can select the directory or file. It will be listed in the
   separated field.

   Then you can select the type of checking.
      * case sensitive filenames for unix systems (e.g. AgE.hTmL)
      * check of anchor links (e.g. age.html#start)
      * list of orphaned files 

   If you don't select anything, the normal check will be executed.

   @{fg fill}Start@{fg text} - starts the check and opens the @{"result window" link "RWind"}.
   @{fg fill}Save@{fg text}  - all infos will be saved into tooltypes
   @{fg fill}Info@{fg text}  - opens a window with info of version and author
                               (like menu: ? | Info)
   @{fg fill}Quit@{fg text}- leaves the program
                               (like menu: Project | Quit)

   The menu: "? | Help" opens this guide.


                                       @{" >>> next >>> " link "RWind"}

@ENDNODE

@NODE "RWind" "Usage - Result Window"
@TOC "MAIN"

@{fg shine}The Result Window@{fg text}
   The script checks the (S)HTM(L) files that have been found in the selected 
   directory. 

   @{fg shine}broken link in:@{fg text}
   In the top left edge of the window you can find all broken links.

   @{fg shine}broken case sensitive link in:@{fg text}
   In the bottom left corner you find links that are broken on Unix systems.

   @{fg shine}broken anchor link in:@{fg text}
   At the top right broken anchor links will be listed.

   @{fg shine}orphaned files:@{fg text}
   And last but not least in the bottom right corner you can find files 
   that are not referenced by actual pages.

   Only those listviews are activated that belong to the selected type
   of checking.

   First, all files will be scaned for anchor links <a name=...>
   After that every file will be checked for all types of links.
   Detected errors will be listed immediately.
   A progress bar tells you the progress of work.

   After checking of files has ended and NO files are listed in any list
   all links work correctly ;-) You are able to upload your new pages to
   the web server.

   If not, you have to work on your files:
   With the button @{fg fill}Info@{fg text} you can get information about the broken link.
        File     : the file, where the broken link is located in
        links to : name of the target file
        at line  : line of the file

        @{fg fill}Edit@{fg text} allows you to manipulate this file with your favorite text
               editor (see @{"configuration" link "Con"}).
        @{fg fill}Cancel@{fg text} will close the info window.

   With the button @{fg fill}I know@{fg text} you can remove the file from the list.
   It will not be deleted from your system!!!

   At @{fg shine}orphaned files:@{fg text} you find the button @{fg fill}Delete@{fg text}.
   Here you can delete the selected file from your system.

   That's all ;-)

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   All broken links will also be reported at log files.
      T:LinkCheckResult          - broken links
      T:LinkCheckResult-Unix     - broken case sensitive links
      T:LinkCheckResult-Anchor   - broken anchor links

    e.g.:
      HD1:Homepages/Age/main.html - next.html - line 123

    This informs you, that a link from main.html to next.html at line 123 doesn't
    work.

